# PART B — Clause-by-Clause Agreement (California v1)

## B0 — How to present it
- Each clause is 1 screen (or 1 card with “Agree”).
- 8–12 clauses max.
- Plain English first, then “Legal summary” dropdown.
- Store acceptance with timestamp in `provider_agreement_acceptance`.

> **Note:** California restricts certain restraints. Avoid overreaching. Focus on **confidentiality + platform integrity + no side payments + standards**. For non-circumvention, use narrower language and have counsel tune.

---

## Clause 1 — Independent Contractor
**Title:** You are an independent business  
**Text:** You are an independent contractor, not an employee of Handled Home. You control your work methods and your team.  
You’re responsible for taxes, permits, insurance, and legal compliance.  
**Button:** I Agree

---

## Clause 2 — Follow SKUs + Levels (Standardized Scope)
**Title:** Perform services using Handled SKUs + Levels  
**Text:** For Handled Home jobs, you agree to perform services according to our **Service Definitions (SKUs)** and **Levels** (scope + time + proof).  
No custom scope changes or “side agreements” for Platform jobs.  
**Button:** I Agree

---

## Clause 3 — Proof-of-Work Required
**Title:** Proof is required for every job  
**Text:** You agree to complete required **photos and checklists** for every job.  
Proof protects you and the customer and keeps support costs low.  
**Button:** I Agree

---

## Clause 4 — No Side Payments / Off-App Transactions
**Title:** All payments must go through Handled Home  
**Text:** You will not accept cash, checks, or off-platform payments for Handled Home jobs, upgrades, or add-ons, unless explicitly authorized in writing by Handled Home.  
**Button:** I Agree

---

## Clause 5 — Professional Conduct & Reliability
**Title:** Be reliable and professional  
**Text:** You agree to be on time, follow access instructions, treat the property respectfully, and communicate professionally.  
Repeated no-shows, late cancellations, or poor conduct can result in suspension or removal.  
**Button:** I Agree

---

## Clause 6 — Scheduling & Route Discipline
**Title:** Follow scheduled windows and route plans  
**Text:** You agree to follow job schedules and route plans provided by Handled Home, and use the app for job status updates.  
If you need to reschedule, you’ll follow platform procedures.  
**Button:** I Agree

---

## Clause 7 — Courtesy Upgrade & Level Recommendations (Policy-Based)
**Title:** Use courtesy upgrades only when allowed  
**Text:** If enabled for your account, you may perform a **Courtesy Upgrade** only according to Handled policy, with required reason codes and proof.  
You may recommend a higher Level for next cycle when needed to meet standards.  
**Button:** I Agree

---

## Clause 8 — BYOC Integrity (No Incentive Abuse)
**Title:** BYOC incentives require integrity  
**Text:** If you invite your customers (BYOC), you agree not to create fake accounts, misrepresent incentives, or manipulate signups.  
Abuse results in immediate removal and forfeiture of unpaid bonuses.  
**Button:** I Agree

---

## Clause 9 — Customer Data & Confidentiality
**Title:** Protect customer and platform information  
**Text:** Customer information and platform operations are confidential.  
You will not use customer data for unrelated marketing or share it outside your business operations for Handled jobs.  
**Button:** I Agree

---

## Clause 10 — Non-Circumvention / Non-Solicitation (California-tuned placeholder)
**Title:** Don’t take Handled Home customers off-platform  
**Plain-English:** If Handled Home introduces you to a customer, you agree not to redirect that customer to pay you outside the platform for the same services, during the period you’re active on Handled Home.  

**Implementation note (important):**
- Keep this clause narrow in v1 to reduce enforceability risk in California.
- Stronger versions should be reviewed by counsel.  
- You can still enforce “no side payments” and “no off-platform billing” for platform-introduced customers.

**Button:** I Agree

---

## Clause 11 — Compliance (Licensing/Insurance)
**Title:** You’ll maintain required licensing and insurance  
**Text:** You agree to maintain required licenses, insurance, and permits for your category and region, and provide updated proof when requested.  
**Button:** I Agree

---

## Clause 12 — Termination & Enforcement
**Title:** We can suspend or remove providers who break standards  
**Text:** Handled Home may suspend or remove providers for fraud, safety issues, repeated proof failures, side payments, or serious customer complaints.  
You may stop using the platform at any time, subject to completing accepted jobs.  
**Button:** I Agree

